Description: Floor and foot sherd of Attic black-glazed pottery bowl; wholly glazed save stand-ring, which is grooved; interior: stamped palmettes and rouletting; inscription cut on underside.
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Sanctuary of the Dioskouroi (Naukratis), Found in the area between the sanctuaries of the Dioskouroi and Apollo (see Petrie 1886, 16)
Excavated/Findspot: Sanctuary of Apollo (Naukratis), Found in the area between the sanctuaries of the Dioskouroi and Apollo (see Petrie 1886, 16)
Bibliographic references: Petrie 1886 / Naukratis. Part I., 1884-85 (pl. XXXV, no. 696)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GA.1687)
